s|TAG_ACTRESS_LONG_DESC|Pamela Anderson was born in Ladysmith, British Columbia, Canada on 01, July 1967. She grew up in Vancouver. She worked for two seasons for the top-ten ABC Television hit series "Home Improvement" (1991) as Tool Time Girl. She then played the role of a lifeguard, C.J. Parker, on internationally famous successful series "Baywatch" (1989). In 1998, she stared on TV show "V.I.P.". She also stared in action comedy Barb Wire (1996). Pamela married to Motley Crue drummer Tommy Lee, and they had two children, Brandon and Dylan. She later dates dated singer Kid Rock until fall of 2003. She was diagnosed with hepatitis C. She is active participant in various organizations, including PETA (People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals).|g
